&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You´ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&g

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hey there! &lt;br&gt;We’re &lt;a href=&quot;https://feverup.com/&quot;&gt;Fever&lt;/a&gt;, the world’s leading tech platform for culture and live entertainment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission? To democratize access to culture and entertainment. With our proprietary cutting-edge technology and data-driven approach, we’re revolutionizing the way people engage with live entertainment. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Every month, our platform inspires over 300 million people in +55 countries (and counting) to discover unforgettable experiences while also empowering event creators with our data and technology, helping them scale, innovate, and enhance their events to reach new audiences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our results? We’ve teamed up with major industry leaders like Netflix, F.C. Barcelona, and Primavera Sound, presented international award-winning experiences, and are backed by several leading global investors! Impressive, right?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To achieve our mission, we are looking for bar-raisers with a hands-on mindset who are eager to help shape the future of entertainment!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ready to be part of the experience?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, let’s discuss this role and what you will do to help achieve Fever’s mission.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and elevate creative execution for high-visibility digital marketing campaigns across Meta, TikTok, YouTube, and emerging platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and deliver best-in-class video and static assets, from key visuals and motion pieces to thumbnails, end screens, hero assets &amp;amp; organic and paid media assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Focus on producing assets with AI tools, defining workflows that accelerate ideation, production, localization, and iteration at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leveraging AI platforms to produce 100% of assets in creative production for paid &amp;amp; organic media, hero assets, landing page assets, editing and other adhoc requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prototype, pitch, and validate new creative formats using insights from performance data, platform trends, and audience behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set creative and technical standards for AI-assisted design and video production, documenting best practices and workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and support junior designers, providing feedback, creative direction, and guidance on both craft and AI usage.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of professional experience in digital design, motion, video, AI production, ideally in fast-paced or performance-driven environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience owning creative projects end-to-end, from concept to execution and iteration, leveraging AI tools to achieve the best outcome in assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of performance marketing creatives and how design decisions impact results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency in tools such as:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Figma, Adobe After Effects, Adobe Premiere, Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Illustrator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generative AI tools for image, video, copy, and ideation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in integrating AI into everyday workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in Spanish and English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based in Madrid.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be a good fit if you…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Think in systems, not just assets, and care about scalability as much as craft.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are proactive, opinionated, and comfortable making decisions, while staying open to feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Balance speed and quality, even under tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &amp;amp; Perks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hey there! &lt;br&gt;We’re &lt;a href=&quot;https://feverup.com/&quot;&gt;Fever&lt;/a&gt;, the world’s leading tech platform for culture and live entertainment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission? To democratize access to culture and entertainment. With our proprietary cutting-edge technology and data-driven approach, we’re revolutionizing the way people engage with live entertainment. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Every month, our platform inspires over 300 million people in +55 countries (and counting) to discover unforgettable experiences while also empowering event creators with our data and technology, helping them scale, innovate, and enhance their events to reach new audiences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our results? We’ve teamed up with major industry leaders like Netflix, F.C. Barcelona, and Primavera Sound, presented international award-winning experiences, and are backed by several leading global investors! Impressive, right?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To achieve our mission, we are looking for bar-raisers with a hands-on mindset who are eager to help shape the future of entertainment!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ready to be part of the experience?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, let’s discuss this role and what you will do to help achieve Fever’s mission.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Behind the user-friendly iOS and Android apps and webpage that work across the world is the engineering team.&amp;nbsp; We are in charge of creating, developing, improving, and maintaining all Fever services so that more people can have an amazing experience. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI is changing how Product Engineering teams operate, and we’re building the team that defines what that looks like at Fever.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a &lt;strong&gt;software engineering role at its core&lt;/strong&gt;. We’re looking for an outstanding Senior Software Engineer — someone who cares about code quality and not just getting things done, but getting them done right — who has built real AI and agent expertise &lt;em&gt;on top of&lt;/em&gt; strong engineering fundamentals, and wants to ship it to production across the whole company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll join the &lt;strong&gt;AI &amp;amp; DevEx area&lt;/strong&gt;, and our mission is bigger than tooling: it’s the &lt;strong&gt;performance of Fever’s entire Product Engineering organization&lt;/strong&gt;. The squad is our unit of work and our target — and a squad is far more than code. It’s product management, product design, and engineering, plus the entire environment around them: the CI/CD pipelines, the monitoring and observability that feed context, the infrastructure a squad’s product runs on, the data people gather and analyze, the way they communicate and coordinate. Almost everywhere in that chain — from a first idea to a shipped, validated feature — there’s something AI can make better, and that’s our mission. We raise the leverage of &lt;em&gt;all&lt;/em&gt; of it, until it compounds across the whole org.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Concretely, your scope spans two sides of the same coin: the &lt;strong&gt;agentic harness&lt;/strong&gt; — the skills, sub-agents, evals, and verification that turn agents into shippable output — and the &lt;strong&gt;delivery substrate&lt;/strong&gt; it runs on — dev environments, CI, the autonomous-delivery rails, and the telemetry that proves it works. You’ll build across this surface as a hands-on senior engineer, partnering with squads across the company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll work on&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The agentic harness.&lt;/strong&gt; Build and improve the skills, sub-agents, guardrails, tools, and verification that make agents produce high-quality output — not just for engineering, but for the entire squad and org.&lt;/li&gt;

